 raízes da equação são chamadas de autovalores, enquanto a solução não-nula correspondente a \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\lambda;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5Clambda\" title=\"\\lambda\" \/\u003E é chamado de autovetor associado com o autovalor \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\lambda;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5Clambda\" title=\"\\lambda\" \/\u003E.\u003Cbr \/\u003E\u003Cbr \/\u003ESendo \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\Delta = tr(A)^2 - 4\\det(A);]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5CDelta%20=%20tr%28A%29%5E2%20-%204%5Cdet%28A%29\" title=\"\\Delta = tr(A)^2 - 4\\det(A)\" \/\u003E, temos três casos: \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\Delta \\succ 0;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5CDelta%20%5Csucc%200\" title=\"\\Delta \\succ 0\" \/\u003E, \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\Delta = 0;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5CDelta%20=%200\" title=\"\\Delta = 0\" \/\u003E e \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\Delta \\prec 0;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5CDelta%20%5Cprec%200\" title=\"\\Delta \\prec 0\" \/\u003E.\u003Cbr \/\u003E\u003Cbr \/\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\"\u003ECaso 1:\u003C\/span\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\Delta \\succ 0;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5CDelta%20%5Csucc%200\" title=\"\\Delta \\succ 0\" \/\u003E\u003Cbr \/\u003E\u003Cbr \/\u003ENesse caso, as raízes são reais e distintas, digamos \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\lambda_1;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5Clambda_1\" title=\"\\lambda_1\" \/\u003E e \u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\lambda_2;]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5Clambda_2\" title=\"\\lambda_2\" \/\u003E tais raízes, ou seja,\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003Cbr \/\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\"text-align: center;\"\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color: #000099;\"\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"font-family: verdana;\"\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\"[;\\lambda_{1,2} = \\frac{tr(A) \\pm \\sqrt{\\Delta}}{2};]\" src=\"http:\/\/thewe.net\/tex\/%5Clambda_%7B1,2%7D%20=%20%5Cfrac%7Btr%28A%29%20%5Cpm%20%5Csqrt%7B%5CDelta%7D%7D%7B2%7D\" title=\"\\lambda_{1,2} = \\frac{tr(A) \\pm \\sqrt{\\Delta}}{2}\" \/\u003E\u003C\/spa